// frontend/src/components/PrintableConnectionForm.js // This component renders a static, print-friendly version of the connection form // with empty fields for manual filling and enhanced UI. // Fields are now presented in a table-like column format (icon, label, empty space). import React from "react"; // Import icons for consistent UI import { Laptop, // For PC Name Router, // For IP Address User, // For Username CheckSquare, // For In Domain (Yes/No) Monitor, // For Operating System Columns, // For Ports Name (general ports) Info, // For Description MapPin, // For Location Split, // For Patch Panel HardDrive, // For Total Ports Server, // For Switch Name, Rack Name Link, // For Source Port ChevronsRight, // For general port Wifi, WifiOff, // For port status } from "lucide-react"; function PrintableConnectionForm() { return ( // Apply overall font and spacing classes to the main container

Network Connection Form

Fill out the details for your network connections.

Date: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}

{/* PC Details Section */}

PC Details

{/* PC Name */}
{" "} {/* Grid for icon, label, empty space */}
{/* IP Address */}
{/* Username */}
{/* In Domain */}
Yes No
{/* Operating System */}
{/* Ports Name */}
{/* Office */}
{/* Description */}
{/* Patch Panel Hops Section */}

Patch Panel Hops

{/* Render 3 hops, 2 in first row, 1 in second */}
{[0, 1, 2].map( ( hopIndex // Render 3 hops ) => (

Patch Panel Hop {hopIndex + 1}

Up {" "} Down
) )}
{/* Switch Details Section */}

Switch Details

Up Down
); } export default PrintableConnectionForm;
